  "event_preview": "Circuit de Monaco is a 3.337 km (2.074 mi) street circuit in Monte Carlo with 19 corners. The 2026 FIA Formula 3 Championship round at Monaco is the second of nine rounds, held June 4-7. The weekend follows a unique schedule with Free Practice on Thursday, Qualifying split into two groups on Friday, and races on Saturday and Sunday.\n\nBruno del Pino, Taito Kato and Enzo Deligny arrive at Monaco as the only drivers with a 100% scoring record from the Melbourne season opener. Van Amersfoort Racing leads the teams' championship for the first time since entering FIA Formula 3, while Campos Racing — the defending team champions from 2025 — will look to respond. Ugo Ugochukwu begins the round leading the drivers' championship after his Melbourne Feature Race victory. The narrow streets and close barriers of Monte Carlo offer little margin for error, making precision in qualifying historically crucial for Feature Race success.\n\nThe FIA Formula 3 qualifying lap record at Monaco belongs to Leonardo Fornaroli, who set a 1:21.685 during qualifying for the 2024 round. The race lap record is held by Paul Aron, who clocked a 1:22.876 during the 2024 Feature Race.",
